title: Falcon 9 launches ocean science mission for NASA and CNES
summary: A Falcon 9 successfully launched an Earth science mission jointly developed by the United States and France to monitor water levels and the effects of climate change.

title: Maxar Technologies acquired by private equity firm in $6.4 billion deal
summary: Maxar Technologies, a space company that gained global attention with its high-resolution satellite images of the Ukraine war, is being acquired by the private equity firm Advent International for $6.4 billion.

title: Rocket Report: Meet the Blue Origin Space Rangers; methane rocket fails in debut
summary: No one has yet stepped forth to win the great methane rocket race.

title: China completes seventh space launch inside 10 days
summary: China launched a Long March 11 solid rocket from Xichang early Friday, completing a campaign of seven orbit launch attempts in just over a week which included the debut of two new launch vehicles.

title: EOI Space forges equity and sales pact with Japan’s NTT Data
summary: EOI Space, the Earth-observation startup formerly known as Earth Observant, attracted its first major customer for ultra-high-resolution imagery drawn from a constellation of satellites destined for very low Earth orbit.

title: Arqit drops plan to operate quantum encryption satellites
summary: British cybersecurity software developer Arqit is looking to sell a partly built satellite after scrapping plans for a space-based quantum encryption network.

title: Space acquisition chief: DoD will buy small satellites, at fixed prices
summary: Frank Calvelli, assistant secretary of the Air Force for space acquisitions and integration, wants acquisition officers to avoid cost-plus contracts and buy satellites at fixed prices

title: NASA Awards Contract to Maintain Webb Telescope Operations
summary: NASA has selected Northrop Grumman Systems Corporation of Redondo Beach, California, to support the James Webb Space Telescope Phase E – Operations and Sustainment contract.

title: NASA, AST & Science Sign Joint Spaceflight Safety Agreement
summary: NASA and AST & Science, a subsidiary of AST SpaceMobile, Inc., have signed a joint agreement to formalize both parties’ strong interest in the sharing of information to maintain and improve space safety.

title: Soyuz MS-22 suffers coolant leak, canceling Russian spacewalk
summary: A planned spacewalk aboard the International Space Station on the evening of Dec. 14 involving cosmonauts Sergey Prokopyev and Dmitri Petelin was canceled due to a coolant leak aboard the Soyuz MS-22 spacecraft.
